Hi @zzborn1022!

The `filterEnd` event is triggered on the table itself. So if you want to target an input, I would use a delegated bind; something like this:

```js
$('table').on('change', '.tablesorter-filter', function(){
  var $this = $(this),
    val = $this.val();
  // do something with$this & val...
});
```

Hi, thanks for your answer.
You are right, i was quick to respond :).

I did more tests and will answer your questions. 

The first example works (without ajax):

filter_selectSource : {
        		// Alphanumeric match (prefix only)
        		// added as select2 options (you could also use select2 data option)
        		2 : function(table, column) {
          			return ['1', '2', 'bla bla'];          			
        		}
      		}	

The second example does not work (with ajax):

filter_selectSource : {
        		// Alphanumeric match (prefix only)
        		// added as select2 options (you could also use select2 data option)
        		2 : function(table, column) {          			
          			return $.getJSON("../admin/callbacks/getSelectFilterSearch.php",function(data){													
			            return data.hasOwnProperty('options') ? data.options : false;			            			            			            
					});
        		}
      		}


The file php called is:

<?php
$arr = array('1','2','bla bla');
echo json_encode(array('options'=>$arr));
?>

My answers to your questions should be ok. Maybe it's a problem of JSON.

Thank you very much!

Hmm, well when the filters are applied, it adds a `display: table-row` style to the row which is overriding the css style. I know it's not encouraged, but I think in this case you might need to use an `!important` flag.

```css
.invisible-table-row {
    display: none !important;
}
```

As for the pager not working, there are only 3 rows in [this demo](), so it doesn't look like it's working, but it is. I did find a bug causing the page count to be off if the first tbody isn't being targetted by the pager (info-only tbody) which I just fixed in the working branch (https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/commit/638d070f3ad3c1ead30c060a7fb5a440546f994e). Please use the updated [pager file](https://github.com/Mottie/tablesorter/blob/working/addons/pager/jquery.tablesorter.pager.js).

