It is running. After some time it died and patroni was able to start another process. But postgresql state was corrupted already (looks like start without specified replica role). It is not clear if state was corrupted by old process or new processes but during last start postgresql writes in logs `database system was shut down at 2017-10-13 14:34:46 UTC` which coresponds to first failed postgresql start with `LOG: could not bind IPv4 socket: Address already in use`.

It looks like this :

1. rm -rf data directory;
2. patroni releases lock and performs failover;'
3. patroni starts bootstrapl;
4. patroni tries to start postgresql but it fails with ` LOG: could not bind IPv4 socket: Address already in use` because old process still running. This start will be references as `first failed postgresql start`;
5. patroni tries to start postgresql but it fails with ` LOG: could not bind IPv4 socket: Address already in use` because old process still running;
6. patroni tries to start postgresql but it fails with ` LOG: could not bind IPv4 socket: Address already in use` because old process still running;
7. patroni tries to start postgresql but it fails with ` LOG: could not bind IPv4 socket: Address already in use` because old process still running;
8. Old process dies with message `LOG: received immediate shutdown request`;
9. Patroni starts postgresql. Postgresql writes in logs time of last shutdown which corresponding to `first failed postgresql start`;
10. Postgresql running at last but cannot resume replication because `FATAL: could not receive data from WAL stream: ERROR: requested starting point 0/A000000 is ahead of the WAL flush position of this server 0/9002FA8`. This can happen because it was started as master.

